<TITLE> US drone attack kills 7 in Pakistan's Waziristan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ISLAMABAD, Jan 17 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A US drone aircraft fired missiles into Pakistan's South Waziristan region on the Afghan border, killing at least seven militants on Sunday, Pakistani security officials said. "The missiles hit a militant compound," a security official told Reuters. "We have reports that seven militants were killed but the death toll could rise." Most of the casualties were foreign fighters, he added. The pilotless drone strikes are a source of friction between the United States and Pakistan, which sees them as a violation of its sovereignty. Washington says they are an effective weapon in tribal areas in northwest Pakistan along the Afghan border seen as a global hub for militants, including senior al Qaeda and Taliban figures. Pakistani Taliban militants issued an audio tape on Saturday purportedly from their leader, Hakimullah Mehsud, denying he had been killed in a US missile strike two days earli
